    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>No. 392.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gurry</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-09-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 30,
                            1886</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Curry informs Mr. Bayard that he has received the latter’s telegrams;
                        that immediate action on their subject has been promised by the minister of
                        state. He requests that the withdrawal of the proclamation of 1884 may be
                        delayed until after a definite report has been made by the legation at
                        Madrid.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
